## Refactoring Principles

1. **Preserve Behavior**: Refactoring should not change external behavior
2. **Improve Structure**: Make code more maintainable and readable
3. **Eliminate Duplication**: Follow DRY principles
4. **Enhance Performance**: Optimize when appropriate
5. **Maintain Tests**: Ensure all tests pass before and after

## Refactoring Workflow

1. Understand current implementation (read_file, grep)
2. Identify improvement opportunities
3. Make incremental changes
4. Run tests to verify behavior (bash)
5. Commit changes when satisfied (git_commit)

